---
import Page from "../comp/page.astro";
---

<Page>
  <main class="max-w-[60ch] mx-auto">
    <h1 class="text-4xl my-6 font-bold">Sampler</h1>
    <p class="text-xl py-3">
      Hi, I love music, I love coding, i love sampler (I have an SP 404 mkII ),
      so i wanted to try build one in the browser. For fun, availability, for
      practice, to use the web audio api, and see how performant it can be.
    </p>
    <p class="text-xl py-3">
      I'm surprised, its not bad, way more could be done here, this is just a
      hacked together first version.
      <br /> WIP & more to come for sure!
    </p>
    <div>
      <a
        href="app"
        class="text-2xl bg-white text-[var(--bg)] py-2 px-2 font-bold"
      >
        {"--> App here"}
      </a>
    </div>
    <ul class="mt-20 flex flex-col gap-3 list-disc ml-4">
      <li>built with web-audio api</li>
      <li>astro & tailwind</li>
      <li class="line-through">First react redux</li>
      <li>then vue for practice</li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://github.com/Britnell/sampler" class="underline"
          >code on github -</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
  </main>
</Page>
